                <th class="text-right px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Bowl Volume (Gal)</th>
                <th class="text-right px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Beach Length (mm)</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100">
              <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50"><td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-mono text-text-light">1</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light">154</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light">2.3</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light">348</td></tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50"><td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-mono text-text-light">2</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light">150</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light">2.8</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light">322</td></tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50"><td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-mono text-text-light">3</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light">140</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light">3.7</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light">267</td></tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50"><td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-mono text-text-light">4</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light">134</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light">4.7</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light">217</td></tr>
              <tr class="bg-gold/10 hover:bg-gold/20"><td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-mono text-text-light font-bold">5</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light font-bold">132</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light font-bold">4.9</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light font-bold">205</td></tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50"><td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-mono text-text-light">6</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light">138</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light">4.2</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light">239</td></tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50"><td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-mono text-text-light">7</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light">146</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light">3.2</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light">295</td></tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50"><td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-mono text-text-light">8</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light">152</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light">2.5</td><td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right text-text-light">341</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p class="text-xs text-text-light italic mb-6">Position 5 (highlighted) = deepest pond at 132&nbsp;mm radius, 4.9 gal bowl volume, 205&nbsp;mm beach. Position 1 = shallowest pond, maximum beach length for cake dewatering.</p>

        <figure>
          <img src="/images/decanter-centrifuge-pond-depth/Decanter-Pond-Depth-Weir-Plate-500.jpg" alt="Decanter eccentric port weir plate showing 8 indexed positions for pond depth adjustment" width="500" height="600" loading="lazy" class="rounded-lg mx-auto" />
          <figcaption class="text-xs text-center text-text-light mt-2">Decanter Pond Depth Weir Plate Setting — eccentric port positions 1–8</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <!-- Summary -->
      <h2 id="summary-section" class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold font-heading text-navy mb-4">Summary</h2>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <p class="text-text-light leading-relaxed mb-3">The pond depth formed within a rotating decanter significantly affects the decanter&rsquo;s performance. Adjusting this depth allows the operator to balance the separated liquid&rsquo;s clarity versus the separated solids&rsquo; dryness.</p>
        <p class="text-text-light leading-relaxed">In other words, decanter centrifuge pond depth is the tool to control the trade-off between centrate clarity and cake dryness.</p>
      </div>

